INSERT INTO bytes.bytes (id, author_id, title, body, code_snippet, language, embedding, type, is_active, created_at, updated_at) VALUES (
  '50e650b9-a54d-440f-be0b-d4dc907b9a53',
  '00000000-0000-0000-0000-000000000001',
  $escape$ONNX Model Registry — Staging, Production, and Opset-Aware Approval Gates with MLflow$escape$,
  $escape$ONNX models stored in MLflow's registry expose three mutable stages per version: `None`, `Staging`, and `Production`. Each `mlflow.onnx.log_model()` call creates a new `ModelVersion` that bundles the full `onnx.ModelProto` — including `opset_import` metadata — critical because an opset-17 model silently falls back to CPU on ORT execution providers that only support opset-15.

The approval workflow maps to `MlflowClient.transition_model_version_stage()`. Typical gate: CI logs the ONNX artifact, spins an `onnxruntime.InferenceSession` against the Staging URI (`models:/name/Staging`), validates the opset, then promotes to `Production` with `archive_existing_versions=True` — atomically retiring the prior champion version.

For canary rollouts, pin ORT sessions to an explicit version number (`models:/resnet50-v2/3`) rather than the `Production` alias. The alias can flip mid-request during a promotion; a pinned URI references an immutable artifact. Always gate on `proto.opset_import[0].version` before promotion — a mismatched opset nukes GPU throughput with no error, just silent CPU fallback on DirectML and CUDA EPs.$escape$,
  $escape$import mlflow, mlflow.onnx, onnxruntime as ort
from mlflow.tracking import MlflowClient

with mlflow.start_run():
    mlflow.onnx.log_model(model, "model", registered_model_name="resnet50-v2")

client = MlflowClient()
client.transition_model_version_stage("resnet50-v2", version=3, stage="Staging")

# Approval gate: validate opset before production promotion
proto = mlflow.onnx.load_model("models:/resnet50-v2/Staging")
assert proto.opset_import[0].version >= 17, "ORT EP requires opset >= 17"

client.transition_model_version_stage(
    "resnet50-v2", version=3, stage="Production", archive_existing_versions=True
)
session = ort.InferenceSession(proto.SerializeToString())$escape$,
  $escape$python$escape$,
